Indianopedia:

"Devolutionism is the defense of the progressive legal reduction -until its total desapearing- of the economic monopoly for patents, copyrights and other intellectual property forms, expanding the public domain with the creations of the last decades. Devolutionism has won its theoretical maturity with the works of Boldrin and Levin (2000)[http://www.micheleboldrin.com/research/aim.html] and its empirical with Heidi Williams studies on human genome patents[http://deugarte.com/gomi/Williams_jmp.pdf]. The result of research is clear: IP is counterproductive to innovation, its original goal)."
(http://lasindias.net/indianopedia/Devolutionism)

